          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-04-02T14:40:30Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Preventing Pandemic Profiting Act</b></p> <p>This bill creates a new criminal offense for price gouging during a state of emergency. </p> <p>Specifically, in a location that has received a state of emergency declaration, the bill prohibits the sale of certain goods or services&#8212;those vital and necessary for consumer health, safety, and welfare&#8212;at an unconscionably excessive price (e.g., a price higher than the average price during the 30-day period before the emergency declaration was made).</p> <p>A violator is subject to fine, a prison term of up to five years, or both.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2020-03-12T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
